<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="U" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Uncivil" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Uncivil,</orth> ill-mannered, impolite, rude: <cit><quote>u. outrages,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. V, 4, 17</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>that rude u. touch,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. V, 4, 17</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>this u. rule,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 2.3.132" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 3, 132</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this is as u. as strange,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.277" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 277</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this u. and unjust extent against thy peace,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 4.1.57" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 57</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>u. lady,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 5.115.57" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 115</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>with civil and u. arms,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.102" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 3, 102</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the u. kerns,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.310" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 310</bibl></cit>. cf. <emph>Incivil.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>